@

We could fetch the raw commit message separately
([[git log --format=%B]]), but that would require an extra subprocess
call per commit.
Instead, we extract the message directly from the [[git show]]
output---it is indented with four spaces---filter it, and reconstruct
the output in place, reusing [[parse_show_sections]] to locate the
boundaries.

<<helper functions>>=
def filter_show_output(show_output):
    """Filter learnlog runs from ``git show`` output.

    Extracts the indented commit message, strips the four-space
    indentation, filters learnlog run blocks, re-indents, and
    reconstructs the full output.  Returns ``None`` if all run
    blocks were filtered out.
    """
    lines = show_output.split("\n")
    header_end, diff_start = parse_show_sections(lines)

    <<extract and filter raw message>>
    <<reconstruct show output>>
@

<<extract and filter raw message>>=
end = diff_start if diff_start is not None else len(lines)
msg_lines = lines[header_end + 1:end]
raw_msg = "\n".join(
    line[4:] if line.startswith("    ") else line
    for line in msg_lines
)
filtered_msg = filter_learnlog_runs(raw_msg)

if not filtered_msg.strip():
    return None
@

<<reconstruct show output>>=
reindented = []
for line in filtered_msg.split("\n"):
    if line:
        reindented.append("    " + line)
    else:
        reindented.append("")

header = lines[:header_end + 1]
diff = lines[end:] if diff_start is not None else []
return "\n".join(header + reindented + diff)
@

Filtering is enabled by default because learnlog runs are never part
of the student's development story---a teacher reviewing the log
should not have to remember a flag to get a clean view.
The [[filter_learnlog]] parameter lets the [[--all]] flag disable it
for debugging or completeness.

<<commit data functions>>=
def get_commit_detail(repo, commit_hash,
                      filter_learnlog=True):
    """Return ``git show`` output for a single commit,
    reordered so the diff appears before the message.

    When ``filter_learnlog`` is ``True`` (the default),
    learnlog's own run blocks are stripped from the commit
    message.  Returns ``None`` if all runs in the commit
    were learnlog runs.
    """
    result = repo.git("show", commit_hash)
    detail = result.stdout

    if filter_learnlog:
        detail = filter_show_output(detail)
        if detail is None:
            return None

    return reorder_commit_detail(detail)
@

