\subsection{Chunking captured I/O into events}
\label{sec:chunk-io}

The I/O log stores interleaved input and output with line
prefixes like [[stdout: hello]] and [[stdin: answer]]
(see \cref{capture}).
Rather than splitting all input and output into two flat
strings, we group consecutive output lines into chunks
separated by input lines.
This preserves the conversational structure of interactive
programs---the student sees a prompt, types a response,
sees more output, types again, and so on.

The algorithm walks the log lines in order, accumulating
consecutive [[stdout:]]/[[stderr:]] lines into a buffer.
When a [[stdin:]] line appears, the buffered output is
flushed as one output chunk, followed by the input line
as an input chunk.
Any trailing output after the last input becomes a final
output chunk.

Each chunk is a tuple of [[(event_type, text)]]:
\begin{description}
\item[\texttt{X-Run.Output}] contains the joined output
  lines (with [[stderr]] merged into output, since
  ProgSnap2 does not distinguish them).
\item[\texttt{X-Run.Input}] contains the text of a single
  [[stdin]] line.
\end{description}

<<export functions>>=
def chunk_io_log(io_log):
    """Chunk an I/O log into output/input event pairs.

    Returns a list of ``(event_type, text)`` tuples where
    ``event_type`` is ``"X-Run.Output"`` or
    ``"X-Run.Input"``.  Consecutive output lines are
    grouped into a single output chunk; each input line
    becomes its own chunk.

    Returns an empty list if ``io_log`` is empty or None.
    """
    if not io_log:
        return []

    chunks = []
    output_buf = []

    for line in io_log.split("\n"):
        if line.startswith("stdin: "):
            if output_buf:
                chunks.append((
                    "X-Run.Output",
                    "\n".join(output_buf),
                ))
                output_buf = []
            chunks.append((
                "X-Run.Input",
                line[len("stdin: "):],
            ))
        elif line.startswith("stdout: "):
            output_buf.append(
                line[len("stdout: "):]
            )
        elif line.startswith("stderr: "):
            output_buf.append(
                line[len("stderr: "):]
            )

    if output_buf:
        chunks.append((
            "X-Run.Output",
            "\n".join(output_buf),
        ))

    return chunks
@

<<test functions>>=
def test_chunk_io_log_basic():
    """Output-input-output pattern produces three chunks."""
    from learnlog.cli import chunk_io_log
    log = (
        "stdout: Enter name:\n"
        "stdin: Alice\n"
        "stdout: Hello Alice!"
    )
    chunks = chunk_io_log(log)
    assert chunks == [
        ("X-Run.Output", "Enter name:"),
