\subsection{The [[clone]] command}
\label{sec:clone}

The [[push]] command delivers a local log to a remote repository, but
we also need the reverse: retrieving a remote log locally.
A teacher cloning a student's pushed learnlog to review it, or a
student moving to a new machine, both need a way to get the
[[.learnlog/]] data from the remote.

The command takes a remote URL, performs a standard [[git clone]] into a
temporary directory, and then moves the resulting [[.git/]] directory
to [[.learnlog/]] in the target working directory.
We use a temporary directory rather than [[git clone --bare]] because
a standard clone produces a properly configured repository with remote
tracking branches---so subsequent [[push]] and [[pull]]
(\cref{sec:pull}) operations work without additional setup.

Like [[push]], we use [[subprocess.run]] with inherited I/O so the
user sees clone progress and can respond to credential prompts.
We deliberately avoid constructing a [[LearnlogRepo]] before the
clone completes, because its constructor auto-initialises an empty
repository when [[.learnlog/]] is absent.

<<typer commands>>=
@app.command()
def clone(
    url: Annotated[
        str,
        typer.Argument(
            help="URL of the remote repository to clone.",
        ),
    ],
    directory: Annotated[
        Optional[pathlib.Path],
        typer.Option(
            "--dir", "-C",
            help=(
                "Target directory for the clone. "
                "Defaults to current directory."
            ),
        ),
    ] = None,
):
    """Clone a remote learnlog repository into .learnlog/."""
    import shutil

    workdir = pathlib.Path(
        directory or os.getcwd()
    ).resolve()
    learnlog_dir = workdir / ".learnlog"

    if learnlog_dir.exists():
        raise SystemExit(
            f".learnlog/ already exists in {workdir}"
        )

    tmpdir = tempfile.mkdtemp(prefix="learnlog-clone-")
    try:
        result = subprocess.run(
            ["git", "clone", url, tmpdir],
            cwd=str(workdir),
        )
        if result.returncode != 0:
            raise SystemExit("Clone failed.")
        shutil.move(
            str(pathlib.Path(tmpdir, ".git")),
            str(learnlog_dir),
        )
    finally:
        shutil.rmtree(tmpdir, ignore_errors=True)

    typer.echo(f"Cloned into {learnlog_dir}")
@

