\subsection{The [[play]] command}

The [[play]] command uses [[resolve_source]] to handle both
directories and bundle files.
When a bundle is used, [[resolve_source]] creates a temporary
directory that we must clean up---hence the [[finally]] block.

The [[-b]] / [[--batch]] flag selects batch mode
(\cref{sec:play-batch}), which prints all commits to standard
output instead of launching the curses viewer.
When the flag is not given explicitly, we auto-detect: if
standard output is not a terminal (for example when piped to
[[less]]), batch mode activates automatically.
This means [[learnlog play | less]] just works without the user
having to remember the flag.

By default, learnlog's own runs are filtered from the output
(\cref{sec:filter-learnlog}).
The [[--all]] / [[-a]] flag disables this filter, showing every
run block including those from [[learnlog play]] and
[[learnlog export]] invocations.

<<typer commands>>=
@app.command()
def play(
    source: Annotated[
        Optional[str],
        typer.Argument(
            help=(
                "Source: directory with .learnlog/ "
                "or a .bundle file. "
                "Defaults to current directory."
            ),
        ),
    ] = None,
    start: Annotated[
        Optional[str],
        typer.Option(
            "--start", "-s",
            help="Commit hash to start playback from.",
        ),
    ] = None,
    batch: Annotated[
        Optional[bool],
        typer.Option(
            "--batch", "-b",
            help=(
                "Print all commits to stdout instead of "
                "the interactive viewer.  Auto-enabled "
                "when stdout is not a terminal."
            ),
        ),
    ] = None,
    show_all: Annotated[
        bool,
        typer.Option(
            "--all", "-a",
            help=(
                "Include learnlog's own runs in the "
                "output."
            ),
        ),
    ] = False,
):
    """Interactively play back the development log."""
    import shutil

    repo, tmpdir = resolve_source(source)
    try:
        commits = get_commits(repo)
        if not commits:
            raise SystemExit("No commits found.")

        start_index = 0
        if start:
            <<find starting commit index>>

        <<choose playback mode>>
    finally:
        if tmpdir is not None:
            shutil.rmtree(tmpdir, ignore_errors=True)
@

When [[batch]] is [[None]] (the user did not pass [[-b]]),
we fall back to TTY detection via [[sys.stdout.isatty()]].
An explicit [[--batch]] or [[--no-batch]] always wins.

<<choose playback mode>>=
filter_learnlog = not show_all
use_batch = (
    batch if batch is not None
    else not sys.stdout.isatty()
)
if use_batch:
    play_batch(repo, commits, start_index,
               filter_learnlog)
else:
    viewer = PlaybackViewer(
        repo, commits, start_index, filter_learnlog,
    )
    viewer.run()
@

Typer's [[CliRunner]] does not connect a real terminal, so
invoking [[play]] through it exercises the batch path
automatically.
We verify that the command succeeds and that every commit
appears in the output:

<<test functions>>=
def test_play_batch_via_cli(workdir):
    """The play command uses batch mode when not a TTY."""
    from learnlog.cli import app
    from typer.testing import CliRunner
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    runner = CliRunner()
    result = runner.invoke(
        app, ["play", str(workdir)]
    )
    assert result.exit_code == 0
    assert "diff --git" in result.output
@

We verify that learnlog's own runs are filtered from playback by
default and that [[--all]] restores them:

<<test functions>>=
def test_play_hides_learnlog_runs(workdir):
    """Learnlog runs are filtered from batch output."""
    from learnlog.cli import app
    from typer.testing import CliRunner
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    t1 = datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 1, 10, 0)
    repo.begin_run("hello.py", [], t1)
    repo.begin_run("learnlog", ["play"], t1)
    runner = CliRunner()
    result = runner.invoke(
        app, ["play", str(workdir)]
    )
    assert result.exit_code == 0
    assert "Script: hello.py" in result.output
    assert "Script: learnlog" not in result.output

def test_play_all_shows_learnlog_runs(workdir):
    """The --all flag includes learnlog runs."""
    from learnlog.cli import app
    from typer.testing import CliRunner
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)
    t1 = datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 1, 10, 0)
    repo.begin_run("hello.py", [], t1)
    repo.begin_run("learnlog", ["play"], t1)
    runner = CliRunner()
    result = runner.invoke(
        app, ["play", "--all", str(workdir)]
    )
    assert result.exit_code == 0
    assert "Script: hello.py" in result.output
    assert "Script: learnlog" in result.output
